  "text": "There is common work with partial evaluation of queries [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . Both address applying blocking operators to long or continuous inputs. Punctuation might be used to help partial operators communicate output that is \"partial\" versus output that is \"correct,\" or assist in computing how close we are to the \"correct\" output.",
